text: The Cadiz Township Joint District No. 2 School building is located in Browntown, Wisconsin. ==History== The building was added to the State Register of Historic Places in 1995 and to the National Register of Historic Places the following year. It currently serves as a private residence. ==References== Category:School buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:Residential buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Green County, Wisconsin Category:Schools in Green County, Wisconsin Category:Defunct schools in Wisconsin Category:Bungalow architecture in Wisconsin Category:School buildings completed in 1921
title: Cadiz Township Joint District No. 2 School
